[+1844] Rush Limbaugh Backs Out of His Promise to Move to Costa Rica
item.description: On his radio show today Rush Limbaugh backed out of his promise to leave the country and move to Costa Rica if health care reform passed. Limbaugh said that he never said that he was going to move there but that, "Once all this gets implemented, I am going there for my health care." Rush will be in Costa Rica when Hannity gets waterboarded.

[+1532] High-fructose Corn Syrup Causes More Weight Gain Than Sugar
item.description: A Princeton University research team has demonstrated that all sweeteners are not equal when it comes to weight gain: Rats with access to high-fructose corn syrup gained significantly more weight than those with access to table sugar, even when their overall caloric intake was the same.

item.title: [+687] Memory Fox: Free Add-on Ends Firefox Memory Leaks
item.description: IDEVFH has just released his update to the Memory Fox Firefox add-on. This add-on recovers Firefox memory leaks by automatically flushing & recovering fragmented orphaned RAM. It's similar to the AFOM add-on, also by IDEVFH, but includes support for Songbird, iTunes and TweetDeck. I use it and have had excellent results.

item.title: [+657] The 30-Year-Old Space Shuttle Flies On 1 MB of RAM!
item.description: The soon-to-be-retired Space Shuttle is 30 years old and remarkably relies on an on-board flight computer much less sophisticated than the phone your reading this on: yup, the craft’s General Purpose Computer uses just one MB of RAM.
